 Here is a JavaScript function that uses regex to extract a three character code from a filename in format "57-1Jn.usfm":

```javascript
function extractCode(filename) {
    var pattern = /^(\d+)-([a-zA-Z0-9]{3})\.usfm$/;
    return filename.match(pattern)[2];
}
```

This function uses a regular expression to match the input string against a pattern that consists of:

1. An optional number at the beginning (`\d+`) followed by a dash (-).
2. A three character code consisting of upper or lower case letters or digits (`[a-zA-Z0-9]{3}`).
3. The filename extension ".usfm" (`.usfm$`).

The function returns the matched group, which is the three character code in this case. If no match is found, it will return `null`.
